The GCD function flowchart

GCD function

This function takes two integers from the user and calculates the greatest common divisor between the numbers.

IF ("not a numeric, non-decimal, positive input"){

     Stop the program and throw an error message.
  }

Let x <- maximum of the two numbers, and y <- minimum.

WHILE y is not 0 {

       divide x by y and let remainder be new variable c.

       let x take on value of y, and y take on value of c.

}

return(the value of x, taking on last value of y before it was 0)

The is_prime function

The is_prime function takes in a single integer and determines whether the value is a prime number or not.

IF("not a numeric, non-decimal, positive input"){

     Stop the program and throw an error message.
}

ELSE IF(x = 2){

       output TRUE
 }

ELSE IF(x = 1 or 0){

       output FALSE
}

FOR(i from 2 to x-1){

     IF(remainder of x divided by i is 0){

       return FALSE
  
 }
     ELSE{

        return TRUE
 }
}

This vector is then modified to take in a vector of integers through the Vectorize function.

The get_factors function

The get_factors function takes in a single integer and outputs the prime factors of the integer.

IF(not a numeric, non-decimal, positive input){

     Stop the program and throw an error message.
}

Create an empty numeric vector.

FOR(i between 1 and x-1){

     IF(remainder of x divided by i is 0){

         IF(i is a prime number){

            add i to empty numeric vector.
          }
     }   
     ELSE{

         add x to empty numeric vector. The only prime factor is itself

      }
  }
